CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A3, reads: "Moving Day - Movers remove the cash register...last piece of equipment to go, as Loendi Club's present location becomes a nostalgic memory. President McEnheimer has a far-away look in his eyes as lone Courier salesman passes famed old residence. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Mover carrying box to Walker's moving van, with two other men standing on sidewalk on right, in front of Loendi Club at 83 Fullerton Avenue, Hill District
